===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|to-night}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}
* [[tonite]] {{qualifier|US|informal}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|toniht|tōniht|lang=ang}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-tonight.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The nighttime of the current day or date; [[this]] [[night]].
#: '''''Tonight''' is the night.''
#: ''I have high hopes for '''tonight'''.''

